      • updatePath

        public void updatePath()
        Calls pathTypeRotate() and creates sprite based on diagnosis

      • pathTypeRotate

        public void pathTypeRotate()
        Based on adjecent paths: diagnoses path rotation and type. Path type 0 = straight, 1 = rAngle, 2 = T, 3 = cross. Rotates is how many 90 degree anticlockwise rotations the source sprite needs. Originally used modular arithmetic to create diagnosis, but this is easier to understand.

      • createImage

        public void createImage()
        Creates sprite based on pathType and rotates

      • assignProperties

        public void assignProperties()
        Determines: 1. Whether it's a terminal tile 2. Adjacent tiles

      • determineWizDists

        public void determineWizDists()
        Method to determine directions to wizard, recursivly calling adjacent tiles. This allows each path to know the optimal direction to the wizard.

      • findTerminality

        public WizardTD.Direction findTerminality()
        Based on a tile's position: 1. Determine if it's a terminal tile 2. If it is, return the direction the edge of the screen is in
        Returns:
        the direction the edge of the screen is in
